entries.meaning: An excessive or sudden increase or flood (of something).

verbs.description: overswell (third-person singular simple present overswells, present participle overswelling, simple past and past participle overswelled)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To swell or rise above (something, especially the rim of a container, the sides of something hollow, etc.).
examples: In some years the river overswells its banks, causing widespread flooding.

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To cause (something) to be too swollen or large; to become too swollen or large.
examples: […]  the rents of lands still grew higher upon every lease that expired, till they have arrived at the present exorbitance; when the frog, overswelling himself, burst at last.
